Azapo won't be closing shop any time soon. that's according to the party's director of elections, Kabelo Bokala. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - Azanian People’s Organization director of elections, Kabelo Bokala says the party won’t be closing shop any time soon. Azapo has failed to attract voters in this year's elections. READ: 2019 Election Results Bokala says the party will work on a strategy to grow its followers. “We can see that Azanian people are looking at things differently and they are also looking at political parties differently. As long as black people are there and their issues are on the table. As long as the land issue is still on there table there is no shutdown,” Bokala said.